subsection.def:
grantee (持證人) means a person to
                whom a permit has been granted or transferred or whose permit has been
                renewed;

licence (牌照) means a licence
                issued under section 5(2)(c) or renewed under section 8(1) to
                operate a karaoke establishment or a provisional licence;

licensee (持牌人) means a person
                to whom a licence has been issued or transferred or whose licence has been
                renewed;

paragraph.continued:
and is for the time being in force, the
                        Secretary
                        for Home and Youth Affairs;

subsection.def:
permit (許可證) means a permit
                granted under section 5(2)(a) or renewed under section 8(1) to
                operate a karaoke establishment or a provisional permit;
